    "problemStatement": "Let F(s,x)F(s, x)F(s,x) be the number of triplets of nonnegative integers whose sum is sss and bitwise xor is xxx.\n\nGiven aaa, bbb, and NNN, find the sum of F(a⋅n,b⋅n)F(a \\cdot n, b \\cdot n)F(a⋅n,b⋅n) for all nnn such that 1≤n≤N1 \\leq n \\leq N1≤n≤N.\n\n\nInput Format\nThe first line of input contains an integer TTT denoting the number of test cases. The description of TTT test cases follows.\n\n\nEach test case consists of a single line containing three space-separated integers: aaa, bbb and NNN.\n\n\n\nOutput Format\nFor each test case, output a single line containing the answer. Since the answer can be very large, only output it modulo 109+710^9 + 7109+7.",
    "constraints": [
      "1≤T≤15001 \\leq T \\leq 15001≤T≤1500",
      "1≤a,b≤301 \\leq a, b \\leq 301≤a,b≤30",
      "1≤N≤10121 \\leq N \\leq 10^{12}1≤N≤1012"
    ],
